"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Rosalia\", \"score\": 0.9980042964257396, \"rank\": 0.00199969433331647, \"text\": \"Rosalia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Rosalia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Rosalia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jagger, 81, in a patterned jacket and shirt, attended alongside his ballerina partner, Melanie Hamrick, 37, in a simple black dress.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Hamrick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melanie Hamrick\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Hamrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melanie_Hamrick\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Banks also opted for a black gown, which was adorned with a blue sash, which could be a nod to one of the colours of the French flag, which also include white and red.\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 819, \"end\": 830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams, a four-time gold medal Olympic winner who won the French Open three times, also brought along something blue, with a small makeup box that she carried as she walked in a three-piece suit.\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 1064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"US rapper Snoop Dogg, who is carrying the Olympic torch on Friday towards the end of the relay, also brought the bling with a world-shaped medallion, and gold suit complete with a pocket watch.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.987265182425769, \"rank\": 0.011168445172365265, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is working as a special correspondent for American TV network NBC, and the city he was born in, Los Angeles, will host the 2028 games.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9986414215161805, \"rank\": 0.0012960690832034103, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\", \"score\": 0.9989870577149313, \"rank\": 0.0008189956085900822, \"text\": \"TV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\"}, {\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999947780115612, \"rank\": 5.151314238758291e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.32308399941403e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One Tree Hillactress Sophia Bush wore a red, scrunched-up, corseted dress, and posed for photos alongside Ashlyn Harris in a metallic gold jumpsuit.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Bush\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophia Bush\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Bush\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophia_Bush\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashlyn_Harris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashlyn Harris\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashlyn_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashlyn_Harris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an Instagram post, they said: \\\"Anna and Pharrell said the dress code is 'medal worthy'.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.106624992246935e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bonus points for home country designers.\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And us?\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We said we will make it (US flag emoji) and (LGBT+ flag emoji) @csiriano understood the assignment #Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997274073812016, \"rank\": 0.0002726668911684